cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with neural networks and their ability to retrieve patterns from noisy inputs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses learning algorithms and constraints on learning patterns, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with artificial intelligence and information retrieval, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) respectively. Finally, the paper mentions image processing, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision).
